divs: Sighting DetailsI was looking out at the morning sky to the SW, toward Witchita Falls when, seemingly out of nowhere, an extremely large, bright,glowing light appeared in the sky. The light was so bright and consuming that it was hard to tell exactly what shape it was, but if pressed I would have to say cylindrical. It flew right over me. If you hold your hand out at arm's length and look at the size of your thumb, that's how big it looked, and how high. It didn't make a sound. It continued on toward the NE and disappeared. The most amazing thing I've ever seen.

Summary: A large golden glowing cylinder shaped object approached from the SW and flew NE silently over my head.
